    <text>
        <body>
            <head>23. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rec5nWAotd8wedNxI">Clark</persName>) to President <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName><note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d23fn1">Source: National Security Council, <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>
                    Institutional Files, Box SR 078, <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 36
                        [<gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss> Negotiations II]. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared
                    by <persName corresp="rec1MI7pNjlwnDZyR">Kraemer</persName> and <persName corresp="rec3WaAgwEDeqcFLV">Linhard</persName>. A stamped notation at the
                    top of the memorandum reads: “signed.”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1982-05-24">May 24, 1982</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Additional Guidance on <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>Should you issue an <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> reflecting the decisions
                reached as a result of the May 21 <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName></gloss> meeting<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d23fn2">See <ref target="#d21">Document 21</ref>.</note> on
                    <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss>?</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Facts</p>
            <p>The <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName></gloss> meeting on May 21 provides the basis for you to issue
                additional guidance on the U.S. <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss> position.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>Formalizing your decisions as a result of that meeting in an <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>, will best ensure their clear transmission and
                timely implementation.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">NO</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">That you approve and sign for release the proposed
                                <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> at Tab A.</hi>
                        <note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d23fn3"><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval. The <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> is printed below as
                                <ref target="#d24">Document 24</ref>.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
